Installation:
============

`fribiditex' uses the `fribidi' library and can be
installed on any operating system. Since I
use Mac OSX, the following instructions 
allow you to compile `fribiditex' on Mac OSX.

Hopefully, the `fribiditex' binary will be included
in TeXLive and so you do not need to compile
it yourself.



Instructions to compile `fribiditex` on Mac OSX:
=====================================

  1) Install `xcode'.
  2) Install `homebrew': http://brew.sh
  3) Install `fribidi': brew install fribidi
  4) Install `autoconf': brew install autoconf
  5) Install `pkg-config': brew install pkg-config
  6) sh autogen.sh
  7) ./configure
  8) make
